 recent shifts in the meaning of the gendered body and representation, and explores the possibilities of a nongendered, gender-optional, or gender-queer future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGender identityxSocial aspects. 0aGender identity. 0aTransgender peoplexSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aaccepted expression.  aactivists.  aeuropean articulations.  agender identity.  ahuman rights advocate.  algbtqia rights.  apolitical activism.  arethinking.  atrans history.  atrans people.  atransgender rights.  aus european relations.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029268040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096610940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966109423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520966109/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles